HEADWORD: Infrequent
<hw>In*fre"quent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>infrequens</ets> : cf. F. <ets>infrequent</ets>. See <er>In-</er>
not, and <er>Frequent</er>.]</ety> <def>Seldom happening or occurring;
rare; uncommon; unusual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The act whereof is at this day <qex>infrequent</qex> or out of
use⟦br⟧
among all sorts of men.</q> <rj><qau>Sir T. Elyot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infrequently</ent>⟦br⟧
